---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Help &amp; Documentation | Ultra Zoom"
  description="Learn how to use the Ultra Zoom browser extension to hover-zoom images on 70+ websites."
  currentPage="help"
  og={{
    url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/help',
    title: 'Help & Documentation | Ultra Zoom',
    description: 'Setup, keyboard shortcuts, supported sites, and troubleshooting for the Ultra Zoom browser extension.',
    image: 'https://ultrazoom.app/images/icon-128.png',
  }}
>
    <main class="main" id="main-content">

        <section class="help-hero">
            <div class="help-hero-text">
                <h1>Ultra Zoom Help</h1>
                <p>Everything you need to get the most out of Ultra Zoom, the hover-to-zoom extension for power browsers.</p>
                <ul class="install-links">
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ultra-zoom/jalclpdejbeamaamcpbolkclpnleagmg" class="install-button chrome" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                            <svg class="install-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
                                <path d="M12 0C8.21 0 4.831 1.757 2.632 4.501l3.953 6.848A5.454 5.454 0 0 1 12 6.545h10.691A12 12 0 0 0 12 0zM1.931 5.47A11.943 11.943 0 0 0 0 12c0 6.012 4.42 10.991 10.189 11.864l3.953-6.847a5.45 5.45 0 0 1-6.865-2.29zm13.342 2.166a5.446 5.446 0 0 1 1.45 7.09l.002.001-3.953 6.848c.313.03.63.047.951.047 6.627 0 12-5.373 12-12 0-1.034-.135-2.035-.377-2.986zM12 8.5a3.5 3.5 0 1 0 0 7 3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0-7z"/>
                            </svg>
                            Install for Chrome
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/ultra-zoom/" class="install-button firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                            <svg class="install-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
                                <path d="M22.207 5.534a11.18 11.18 0 0 0-2.455-3.218c.472.869.744 1.79.864 2.352a9.597 9.597 0 0 0-3.678-3.533c-2.057-1.17-4.228-1.32-5.2-1.238a9.747 9.747 0 0 0-5.393 2.138c-.346.3-1.178 1.095-1.884 2.268-.58 1.024-.876 1.963-1.034 2.608a10.783 10.783 0 0 1 2.873-3.312c3.617-2.746 8.239-2.227 8.694-2.174l.03.003c-2.282.103-4.267.8-5.725 1.753A10.143 10.143 0 0 0 6.32 6.8 8.505 8.505 0 0 0 4.25 9.87a7.106 7.106 0 0 0-.143 4.093 8.154 8.154 0 0 0 1.446 3.143 8.482 8.482 0 0 0 2.875 2.455A8.91 8.91 0 0 0 12 20.634a8.62 8.62 0 0 0 3.71-.818 8.177 8.177 0 0 0 2.925-2.283 7.775 7.775 0 0 0 1.503-3.2 7.236 7.236 0 0 0-.115-3.582 6.687 6.687 0 0 0-1.57-2.815c.216.407.37.838.467 1.283a5.845 5.845 0 0 1-.453 3.677 6.11 6.11 0 0 1-2.36 2.629A6.47 6.47 0 0 1 12 16.638a6.596 6.596 0 0 1-2.735-.59 6.17 6.17 0 0 1-2.187-1.703 5.763 5.763 0 0 1-1.147-2.421 5.217 5.217 0 0 1 .146-2.8 5.494 5.494 0 0 1 1.39-2.25c.22-.21.461-.406.72-.577a4.58 4.58 0 0 1 1.604-.72A3.764 3.764 0 0 1 12 6a3.72 3.72 0 0 1 2.18.686 3.51 3.51 0 0 1 1.28 1.74c.084.26.13.53.137.802a2.333 2.333 0 0 0-.764-.822A2.23 2.23 0 0 0 13.6 8.06a2.189 2.189 0 0 0-1.625.687 2.226 2.226 0 0 0-.617 1.657c0 .91.554 1.695 1.343 2.033a2.47 2.47 0 0 0 .939.195 2.404 2.404 0 0 0 1.703-.725 2.494 2.494 0 0 0 .697-1.812c0-.044 0-.088-.003-.132.005.002.397 1.04.095 2.324a4.084 4.084 0 0 1-1.286 2.14 4.32 4.32 0 0 1-2.416 1.065 4.476 4.476 0 0 1-2.655-.42 4.207 4.207 0 0 1-1.866-1.735 4.017 4.017 0 0 1-.535-2.458c.055-.855.35-1.67.85-2.35a4.85 4.85 0 0 1 .953-.93c-1.3.41-2.347 1.255-3.015 2.308A5.593 5.593 0 0 0 5.3 13.357a5.53 5.53 0 0 0 .882 3.27 5.834 5.834 0 0 0 2.603 2.178 6.216 6.216 0 0 0 3.353.522 6.022 6.022 0 0 0 3.094-1.298 5.683 5.683 0 0 0 1.829-2.84c.027-.09.049-.182.07-.273l.003.003a8.063 8.063 0 0 0 .319-2.39c-.012-1.043-.225-2.044-.654-2.914a7.14 7.14 0 0 0-3.903-3.6A7.61 7.61 0 0 0 9.39 5.31a7.18 7.18 0 0 0-3.355 1.588A7.034 7.034 0 0 0 3.99 9.91a6.786 6.786 0 0 0-.154 3.598 6.998 6.998 0 0 0 1.562 3.157 7.399 7.399 0 0 0 3.005 2.201A7.813 7.813 0 0 0 12 19.5a7.667 7.667 0 0 0 3.737-.936 7.26 7.26 0 0 0 2.752-2.592 6.885 6.885 0 0 0 1.135-3.545 6.655 6.655 0 0 0-.717-3.374 7.518 7.518 0 0 0-1.14-1.546c.61.16 1.206.443 1.762.854.443.333.852.714 1.237 1.132a9.53 9.53 0 0 1-.062-2.403c.06-.456.15-.898.284-1.322-.42-.42-.887-.817-1.393-1.178-.534-.378-1.098-.698-1.68-.96.007-.037.013-.075.022-.112a6.793 6.793 0 0 0-.028-3.204 11.018 11.018 0 0 1 4.297 4.22z"/>
                            </svg>
                            Install for Firefox
                        </a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <img src="/images/icon-128.png" alt="Ultra Zoom extension icon" class="help-hero-icon" width="96" height="96">
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="getting-started">
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <p>Ultra Zoom adds instant hover-to-zoom to images across 70+ websites. Follow these steps to get set up:</p>
            <div class="help-screenshot">
                <img src="/images/ultra_zoom_screen_1.png" alt="Ultra Zoom welcome page showing how it works step by step" width="800" height="600" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li class="step-item">
                    <span class="step-number">1</span>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <strong>Install the extension</strong>
                        <p>Add Ultra Zoom from the <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ultra-zoom/jalclpdejbeamaamcpbolkclpnleagmg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chrome Web Store</a> or <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/ultra-zoom/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firefox Add-ons</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="step-item">
                    <span class="step-number">2</span>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <strong>Visit any supported site</strong>
                        <p>Go to Google Images, Amazon, Reddit, Twitter/X, Instagram, YouTube, or any of the 70+ supported websites.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="step-item">
                    <span class="step-number">3</span>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <strong>Hover over an image</strong>
                        <p>Move your mouse over any image thumbnail. The full-size version appears instantly in an overlay.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="step-item">
                    <span class="step-number">4</span>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <strong>Dismiss the overlay</strong>
                        <p>Move your mouse away or press <code>Esc</code> to close the zoomed view.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="keyboard-shortcuts">
            <h2>Keyboard Shortcuts</h2>
            <p>Ultra Zoom is built for power users. These shortcuts work while an image overlay is active:</p>
            <table class="shortcuts-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Shortcut</th>
                        <th>Action</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>Esc</kbd></td>
                        <td>Close the current zoom overlay</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>Scroll Up / Down</kbd></td>
                        <td>Zoom in or out on the displayed image</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>&larr;</kbd> / <kbd>&rarr;</kbd></td>
                        <td>Navigate to the previous or next image in a gallery</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>?</kbd></td>
                        <td>Open the keyboard shortcut help overlay</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>Z</kbd></td>
                        <td>Toggle theater mode (full-window view)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>G</kbd> <kbd>T</kbd> <kbd>N</kbd> <kbd>Y</kbd> <kbd>Q</kbd> <kbd>J</kbd></td>
                        <td>Reverse image search the hovered image (Google, TinEye, Yandex, and more)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>C</kbd></td>
                        <td>Copy current image at the adjusted size <span class="badge-pro">Pro</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>M</kbd></td>
                        <td>Mute or unmute previewed video <span class="badge-pro">Pro</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>&uarr;</kbd> / <kbd>&darr;</kbd></td>
                        <td>Adjust previewed video volume <span class="badge-pro">Pro</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><kbd>,</kbd> / <kbd>.</kbd></td>
                        <td>Step video frame backward / forward <span class="badge-pro">Pro</span></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="supported-sites">
            <h2>Supported Sites</h2>
            <p>Ultra Zoom ships with optimized plugins for these websites, with more added regularly:</p>
            <ul class="site-grid">
                <li>Google Images</li>
                <li>Amazon</li>
                <li>Reddit</li>
                <li>Twitter / X</li>
                <li>Instagram</li>
                <li>Facebook</li>
                <li>YouTube</li>
                <li>Tumblr</li>
                <li>DeviantArt</li>
                <li>Pinterest</li>
                <li>Flickr</li>
                <li>Imgur</li>
                <li>ArtStation</li>
                <li>Pixiv</li>
                <li>eBay</li>
                <li>Etsy</li>
                <li>Steam</li>
                <li>Wikipedia</li>
                <li>GitHub</li>
                <li>and 50+ more&hellip;</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="help-screenshot">
                <img src="/images/ultra_zoom_screen_3.png" alt="Plugins tab showing per-site toggle switches for supported websites" width="800" height="600" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <p class="help-note">Ultra Zoom can also be enabled globally for any website not on the list via the extension popup.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="per-site-control">
            <h2>Per-Site Control</h2>
            <p>You decide where Ultra Zoom is active:</p>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Master toggle:</strong> click the Ultra Zoom toolbar icon and flip the main switch to enable or disable the extension everywhere.</li>
                <li><strong>Per-site toggle:</strong> while on any website, click the toolbar icon and use the site-specific switch to disable Ultra Zoom for that domain only.</li>
                <li><strong>Global mode:</strong> enable "All sites" in the popup to activate Ultra Zoom on websites that don't have a dedicated plugin.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="free-features">
            <h2>Free Features</h2>
            <p>Every install ships with the full plugin catalogue and these power features at no cost:</p>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Theater Mode</h3>
                    <p>Press <kbd>Z</kbd> while hovering to expand the image into a full-window view, ideal for reading small text or inspecting detail.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Reverse Image Search</h3>
                    <p>Press <kbd>G</kbd>, <kbd>T</kbd>, <kbd>N</kbd>, <kbd>Y</kbd>, <kbd>Q</kbd>, or <kbd>J</kbd> on any zoomed image to look it up on Google, TinEye, Yandex, and other engines in a new tab.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Basic Gallery Navigation</h3>
                    <p>Tap <kbd>&larr;</kbd> / <kbd>&rarr;</kbd> while a zoom overlay is open to step through the previous and next images in the gallery without leaving the page.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Hover History</h3>
                    <p>Your last 50 hovered images are saved locally so you can re-open one you scrolled past — without sending anything to a server.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Community URL Rules</h3>
                    <p>Ship-without-update support for new sites: pull the latest community rules pack from the popup and unlock more domains without waiting for a release.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Premium Site Plugins</h3>
                    <p>Every site plugin (Instagram, Amazon, Pinterest, Reddit, eBay, and the rest) is included free, with full-resolution sources where available.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="pro-features">
            <h2>Pro Features</h2>
            <p>Upgrade to Pro to unlock additional capabilities:</p>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Video Preview &amp; Playback Controls</h3>
                    <p>Hover videos to preview them in place, then mute with <kbd>M</kbd>, scrub with <kbd>,</kbd>/<kbd>.</kbd>, and adjust volume with <kbd>&uarr;</kbd>/<kbd>&darr;</kbd> — without opening the source page.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Advanced Gallery</h3>
                    <p>Open a filmstrip, run a slideshow, and batch-download every image in the active gallery in a single keystroke.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Hover History Power-ups</h3>
                    <p>Bump history capacity to 1,000 entries with full-text search and export to CSV so you can find any image you previewed this month.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Image Copy</h3>
                    <p>Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>C</kbd> while an image is zoomed to copy it at the adjusted size directly to your clipboard.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Custom &amp; Extended URL Rules</h3>
                    <p>Write your own URL rewrite rules to teach Ultra Zoom about a private CDN, internal tool, or any site we don&rsquo;t cover yet.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Settings Sync</h3>
                    <p>Your toggles, rules, and history sync across up to 3 devices through your Ultra Zoom account.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="help-screenshot">
                <img src="/images/ultra_zoom_screen_4.png" alt="Account settings showing Pro upgrade options and pricing tiers" width="800" height="600" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <p class="pro-note">Pro plans start with a 7-day free trial. <a href="/pricing">See current plans and pricing</a> &mdash; managed through Stripe, supports up to 3 devices.</p>
            <p class="pro-cta">
                <a href="/pricing" class="pro-cta-btn">See Pro plans</a>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="troubleshooting">
            <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Ultra Zoom isn't working on a site I expect it to support</h3>
                    <p>Click the toolbar icon and make sure the extension is enabled both globally and for that specific site. If the site isn't in the supported list, try enabling "All sites" mode in the popup.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>The zoom overlay flickers or disappears immediately</h3>
                    <p>This can happen on sites with aggressive hover styles. Try moving your mouse slowly and steadily over the image rather than quickly. If the issue persists on a specific site, <a href="/contact">let us know</a> and we'll investigate.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>The extension toolbar icon is missing</h3>
                    <p>Click the puzzle-piece icon in Chrome or the extensions menu in Firefox to find Ultra Zoom and pin it to your toolbar.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Ultra Zoom conflicts with another extension</h3>
                    <p>Try disabling other extensions one at a time to identify the conflict. Common conflicts occur with other image-handling or zoom extensions. <a href="/contact">Report the conflict</a> so we can investigate a fix.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>My Pro license isn't being recognized</h3>
                    <p>Make sure you're logged in with the same account used during purchase. If the problem continues, contact us at <a href="mailto:boden@lostrabbitdigital.com">boden@lostrabbitdigital.com</a> with your order details.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section guide-faq" id="faq">
            <h2>FAQ</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Is Ultra Zoom free?</h3>
                    <p>Yes. Core hover-to-zoom across 70+ sites is completely free, along with theater mode, reverse image search, basic gallery navigation, and hover history. <a href="#pro-features">Pro features</a> (video playback controls, advanced gallery, image copy, custom URL rules) start with a 7-day free trial &mdash; <a href="/pricing">see current plans</a>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Does Ultra Zoom collect my data?</h3>
                    <p>No. Ultra Zoom does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data or browsing history. It operates entirely within your browser. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Which browsers are supported?</h3>
                    <p>Ultra Zoom works on Chrome, Edge, Brave, and other Chromium-based browsers via the Chrome Web Store, and on Firefox via Firefox Add-ons.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How do I request support for a new website?</h3>
                    <p>Send us the site URL at <a href="mailto:boden@lostrabbitdigital.com">boden@lostrabbitdigital.com</a> and we'll update the extension to support it.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I use Ultra Zoom on sites not in the supported list?</h3>
                    <p>Yes. Enable "All sites" mode in the extension popup to activate basic hover-to-zoom on any website. Results may vary depending on how the site structures its images.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-install-cta">
                <p><strong>Ready to try it?</strong> Install Ultra Zoom free for Chrome or Firefox.</p>
                <ul class="install-links">
                    <li><a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ultra-zoom/jalclpdejbeamaamcpbolkclpnleagmg" class="install-button chrome" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install for Chrome</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/ultra-zoom/" class="install-button firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install for Firefox</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="contacts-section" id="contacts">
            <h2>Contacts</h2>
            <p>Have a question or need help? Use our <a href="/contact">contact form</a> or email us directly at <a href="mailto:boden@lostrabbitdigital.com">boden@lostrabbitdigital.com</a>.</p>
        </section>

    </main>
</BaseLayout>
